WALTHER PISTOL!  This is the excellent WALTHER P22 Pistol.  The P22 is a 3/4-size rimfire rendition of the famous Walther P99 center-fire pistol.
This is the excellent WALTHER P22 Pistol.  The P22 is a 3/4-size rimfire rendition of the famous Walther P99 center-fire pistol.
FEATURES:
Actions:  This Walther is a HAMMER-Fired pistol and enables both Double Action and Single Action firing for all types of shooting fun.   The External Hammer easily pulls back for convenient shooting.  Trigger pulls for Double Action and Single Action firing are excellent.  Nice, crisp trigger break!

Safeties:  Slide-mounted safety on both sides that blocks the firing pin so the hammer can be manually lowered safely. It also has a magazine disconnect safety so the gun won’t fire without the magazine inserted and a paddle-style magazine release that can be used by right- or left-handed shooters.
Magazine is constructed of stainless steel with a polymer follower and bump pad. 10-shot capacity.
Very handy ambidextrous magazine release located at the bottom rear of the trigger guard.
Sights: ramp front sight with a white dot pressed into the slide and a polymer rear sight adjustable for windage with two white dots.  Excellent sighting as there is plenty of light between the front sight blade and the rear sight.
Picatinny accessory rail for the mounting of lights, lasers and other accessories.
Low recoil make it easy for anyone to shoot.
Accuracy:  I shot great with bulk ammo and even better with CCI Velocitor and Winchester Power Points.

postcontent: This is a Model 1920 Commercial DWM Crown-N proofed Luger in .30 caliber. It is all original, has all matching serial numbers (grip frame, receiver, barrel, bolt assembly, trigger, sideplate), and has no import marks. It is not a “GERMANY”-marked export gun, and it has the proper “GESICHERT” marking under the safety lever and the proper “GELADEN” marking on the extractor. The grips and the wood-bottom magazine are not numbered, which is correct for this model. postcontent: Used Marlin 336CS 30/30 Lever Action Rifle.  Used in good condition.  The stock shows some small scuffs and dents.From the research I've done, the CS model was released in the mid 80's and added a cross bolt safety to the rifle.  That safety is extremely useful when unloading the rifle after a hunt.  This is typically done by cycling the action, which cycles the rounds through the rifle and ejects them out.  The problem is it also pulls the hammer back, increasing the risk of accidentally discharging the weapon if you're not careful.  The cross bolt safety eliminates that potential, making it a great addition to an already great firearm.
